"n.序言 【英】 n. 序言(introduction) 【考】 反义词：epilogue(后 记) 【记】 pre(前面)+face(脸面 )→前面的脸→开端 【例】 The author wrote a new preface for the second edition of her book. n. 序言(介绍一本书的预备性陈述) 【记】pre前, face脸－书前面的脸－序言 【参】prefigure(v 预示); figure(v 描绘; 塑造) 【类】overture: symphony = preface: book序曲在交响乐的前面 = 前言在书的前面 【反】epilogue(n 结语; 尾声) 【记】前面的脸，书前面的脸就是序言 preface (n.)  late 14c., from Old French preface ""opening part of sung devotions"" (14c.) and directly from Medieval Latin prefatia, from Latin praefationem (nominative praefatio) ""fore-speaking, introduction,"" in Medieval Latin ""prologue,"" noun of action from past participle stem of praefari ""to say beforehand,"" from prae ""before"" (see pre-) + fari ""speak"" (see fame (n.)). preface (v.)  1610s, from preface (n.). Related: Prefaced; prefacing."
